Pure SSH Tunnel
You can tell SSH to listen on the Public IP and forward directly to the GPU. This is faster, supports WebSockets, and uses less CPU.
Run this command on the Public Server:
code
Bash
# -g: Allows remote hosts to connect to local forwarded ports (Gateway mode)
# -L 54302:127.0.0.1:54302: Listen on Public:54302 -> Forward to GPU:54302
ssh -p 41280 -g -L 54302:127.0.0.1:54302 root@localhost -N
Note: If your SSH version is old and -g doesn't work as expected, you can specify the bind address explicitly:
code
Bash
ssh -p 41280 -L 0.0.0.0:54302:127.0.0.1:54302 root@localhost -N